co2Values.comment:
co2-calculation: Assumption enteric fermentation most similar to chicken. However, different feed efficiency conversion ratio. Ratio 3.99/2.19 = 1.82
CO2-value of chicken EDB = 3.6 kg CO2/kg Fleisch -> 3.6 * 1.82 = 6.55 kg CO2e/kg
 calculation-process-documentation: Feed conversion efficiency of rabbits kg concentrate/kg product = 3.99. That of pork 3.23 and that of chicken 2.19. Part of enteric CH4 in total greenhouse emissions for rabbit 2.3%, pork 6.1% and chicken 1.8%.

Calculation alternative: from reference 1: rabbit meat 83.2 kg CO2e/kg protein. Reference 2: protein content of rabbit meat is around 20%. 83.2*0.2 = 16.64 kg CO2e/kg -> value seems very high
Chicken 25.9 kg CO2e/kg protein. Protein content is around 30% -> 7.77 kg CO2e = double as high as our value in the EDB. Therefore rabbit = 16.64/2 = 8.32 kg CO2e/kg

Reasons for high CO2-value of rabbit meat: low meat yield (50%), lots of manure, high mortality, longer storage time in supermarket (3)
